      • readString

        public void readString()
        Method readString(): - Reads characters from standard input and stores values in numbList array. - Characters are space delimited. - Throws exceptions on failures.

      • isValid

        public boolean isValid()
        Returns:
        true if: 1. numbList contains only whole numbers, AND 2. numbList has no duplicates, AND 3. size of numbList forms a perfect square. return false otherwise.

      • isMagic

        public boolean isMagic()
        Returns:
        true if numbList forms a magic square. return false otherwise.
